[Student "S"]
[Deal "E:AK73.QJ2.J5.KQJ6 J94.A93.874.T872 Q865.K764.A32.54 T2.T85.KQT96.A93"]
[Auction "E"]
1NT pass 2Cpass2S pass 2S pass 3S pass 4S pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{WEST has a poor 9 points, but does have two 4-card Majors. So he uses Stayman.

When EAST bids ♠s, WEST isn't strong enough to bid game herself, so she temporizes

with a 3♠ invitation.

EAST has a full 17 points so he accepts the invitation.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
{Baker Bidpractice/Set4 15}
[Dealer "S"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Student "S"]
[Deal "S:KQ.AQ75.KT9.QJ84 2.JT863.8432.AK6 JT8765.9.AQ5.T72 A943.K42.J76.953"]
[Auction "S"]
1NT pass 2H pass 2S pass 3S pass 4S pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{NORTH, with 9 points and a 6-card suit, knows they should play in ♠s.

The question is: how high?

NORTH transfers SOUTH to ♠s, then invites by raising to 3♠.

SOUTH has only two trumps, (good ones, admittedly), but she has a maximum 17 point hand.

So she bids the ♠ game.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]

